15/10/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu attended the opening ceremony Thursday (October 14th) of a new crossing point linking Greek and Turkish-run parts of the divided island. 
The Limnitis/Yesilirmak crossing, in the island's remote northwest, is the seventh between the two sides. 
EU Enlargement Commissioner Stefan Fuele and the UN Secretary-General's special adviser on Cyprus, Alexander Downer, also attended the ceremony. 
Fuele said that opening the crossing is an encouraging signal. 
(AP, Anadolu news agency, Reuters - 14/10/10)
